name: California - Married filing jointly high income
description: Married couple earning $250,000 annually in California - high income with progressive state tax

sources.description: Calculated using 2025 federal and CA state tax tables
sources.notes: Federal: Taxable $250,000 - $31,500 = $218,500. Brackets up to 24%: ~$41,967. CA: Taxable $250,000 - $11,080 = $238,920. CA progressive brackets up to 9.3%: ~$17,050. FICA: SS capped at $176,100 = $10,922.20, Medicare $250k * 1.45% = $3,625. Total: ~$72,842
